cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CY 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with evaluating grammatical error correction systems. It could also belong to cs.LG (Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves machine learning and natural language processing. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as neural networks are commonly used in GEC systems. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.CY (Computers and Society) as it discusses the reliability of GEC metrics and provides a benchmarking platform for GEC output.
